  "prompt": "How do I get call history for my Airtel prepaid number?",
  "response": "To obtain the call history for your Airtel prepaid number, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Airtel Thanks App**: \n   - Download and install the Airtel Thanks app from the Google Play Store or Apple App Store if it's not already on your device.\n   - Log in using your Airtel prepaid number.\n   - Once logged in, navigate to the 'Usage' section where you can view details of your recent calls, SMS, and data usage. Note that the app may only show limited call history details.\n\n2. **Airtel Website**:\n   - Visit the official Airtel website and log in to your account using your mobile number and OTP.\n   - Go to the 'My Account' section, then check under 'Usage & Charges' or a similar tab for call history. The detailed call history might be limited here as well.\n\n3. **Customer Care**:\n   - Call Airtel customer care by dialing 121 from your Airtel number.\n   - Request a detailed call history. They may send it to your registered email ID or offer other means to access it.\n   - Note: You might be required to verify your identity for security purposes.\n\n4. **Airtel Store or Service Center**:\n   - Visit a nearby Airtel store or service center.\n   - Carry a valid ID proof and request a detailed statement of your call history.\n   - They will guide you on how to obtain this information; some charges might apply for a physical statement.\n\nRemember that obtaining call history may be subject to Airtel's privacy policies and terms of service, and detailed records may only be available for a limited period of the past months.",
